article_title: House Votes to File Supreme Court Brief Opposing Obama Immigration Plan
article_text:
WASHINGTON—The House voted largely on party lines Thursday to authorize the GOP-controlled chamber to file a legal brief in a Supreme Court case examining the Obama administration’s executive actions on immigration.

All Democrats and five Republicans opposed the measure, which passed in a 234-186 vote. The five Republicans to vote against the measure were Florida Reps. Carlos Curbelo, Mario Diaz-Balart and Ileana Ros-Lehtinen, as...
